g.text: System
UC01: As an unregistered user, I want to display listed properties.
UC02: As an agent, I can publish any sale announcement on the system, for example received through a phone call.
UC03: As a system administrator, I want to register a new employee.
UC04: As an owner, I intend to submit a request for listing a property sale or rent, choosing the responsible agent.
UC05: As a system administrator, I want to register a store.
UC06: As a system administrator, I want to specify states, districts and cities in the system.
UC07: As an unregistered user, I want to register in the system to buy, sell or rent properties.
US08: As an agent, I intend to see the list of property announcement requests
made to myself, so that I can post the announcement
US09: As a client, I want to leave a message to the agent to schedule a visit to a property of my interest
US10: As a client, I place an order to purchase the property, submitting the order amount
US11: As an agent, I want to list real estate purchase orders to accept or decline a purchase order for a property.
After accepting or declining, an email notification should be sent to the customer
US12: As a system administrator, I want to import information from a legacy system
that has been in use in several agencies
US13: As a network manager, I want to list all employees working in every store of the network
US14: As a client, I want to read the response for the appointment requests, to accept or reject it
US15: As an agent, I intend to list all booking requests for properties managed by me.
US16: As an agent, when viewing a booking request, I want to respond to the user that scheduled the visit.
US17: As a network manager, I want to list all deals made.
US18: As a store manager, I intend to analyse the deals (only sale of houses and apartments) made.
In particular, I intend to compare property sale values with the forecast values.
The prediction of the value of the business/property must
be estimated based on the characteristics of the property and using linear and multilinear regression algorithms.
US19: As a network manager, I want to divide the set of all stores into two subsets, so that the
total number of properties of the stores between the two subsets is the closest possible.
US20: As a client, I want to read the response for the appointment request, to accept or reject it.
US21: As an agent, at the end of the visit, I want to register the visit and the opinion about the business.
